desc: HIST3H3 encodes the histone variant H3.1t, which is a replication coupled histone variant of unknown physiologic and pathological functions (PMID: 21481529, 26527279, 25539924). Histone molecules allow for the effective packaging of DNA in the nucleus and are built out of nucleosomes assembled from histone proteins H2A, H2B, H3 and H4(PMID: 11498575).
articles/1/title: Analysis of the Histone H3.1 Interactome: A Suitable Chaperone for the Right Event.
articles/2/title: A prognostic multigene classifier for squamous cell carcinomas of the larynx.
articles/3/title: Incorporation of histone H3.1 suppresses the lineage potential of skeletal muscle.

desc: The HIST3H3 gene encodes H3.1t, an H3 histone variant.
